<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Day 2: Trek from Kafnu to Mulling</b></p>















<ul type="discd">
 <li>Stay:
     Riverside campsite</li>
 <li>Trek
     Distance: ~11 km</li>
 <li>Trek
     Duration: 8–9 hours approx.</li>
 <li>Destination
     Altitude: Mulling – 3,250 m / 10,700 ft</li>
 <li>Grade:
     Moderate to Challenging</li>
</ul>















<p class="MsoNormalM">After a hearty breakfast at the homestay, the real adventure
begins as you step onto the trail leading out of Kafnu. The path is initially
wide and easy to follow but soon narrows as you leave the village behind. Your
walk takes you through tall pine and deodar forests, their fragrance mixing
with the crisp mountain air.</p>















<p class="MsoNormalM">Along the way, you’ll come across apple orchards and even
get a glimpse of the underground hydro project, a fascinating contrast to the
natural landscape. Soon after, you cross the sparkling Bhaba River and enter a
thick stretch of oak and pine forest. From here, the climb becomes steeper,
testing your stamina as you ascend towards Jhandi Top.</p>















<p class="MsoNormalM">The effort is rewarded with breathtaking views of the
Kinnaur and Spiti ranges. A final push through alpine meadows brings you to the
serene campsite at Mulling, beautifully set by the riverside—an ideal spot to
rest and soak in the wilderness.</p>                           </div>
