<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Day 3: Trek from Mulling to Kara</b></p>















<ul type="discd">
 <li>Stay:
     Campsite under the stars</li>
 <li>Trek
     Distance: ~6 km</li>
 <li>Starting
     Altitude: Mulling – 3,250 m / 10,700 ft</li>
 <li>Destination
     Altitude: Kara – 3,550 m / 11,700 ft</li>
 <li>Grade:
     Easy to Moderate (gradual ascent)</li>
</ul>















<p class="MsoNormalM">The day begins with the soothing sound of the river beside
your campsite. Today’s trek is shorter and less demanding compared to the
previous stretch, giving you more time to enjoy the surroundings.</p>















<p class="MsoNormalM">A steady climb leads you through wide meadows dotted with
wildflowers and streams cascading down the slopes. After crossing a sparkling
waterfall, the trail continues gently alongside the river. The serene walk
opens into expansive pastures where you’ll pitch your tents at Kara.</p>















<p class="MsoNormalM">The Kara campsite is a beautiful high-altitude meadow,
surrounded by mountain ridges and blessed with stunning valley views—a perfect
place to relax and rejuvenate before the next leg of your journey.</p>                           </div>
