<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Day 4: Trek from Kara to Pushtirang</b></p>















<ul type="discd">
 <li>Stay:
     Campsite at Pushtirang</li>
 <li>Trek
     Distance: ~5 km</li>
 <li>Trek
     Duration: 3–4 hours approx.</li>
 <li>Starting
     Altitude: Kara – 3,550 m / 11,700 ft</li>
 <li>Destination
     Altitude: Pushtirang – 4,100 m / 13,500 ft</li>
 <li>Grade:
     Easy to Moderate (gradual ascent)</li>
</ul>















<p class="MsoNormalM">As dawn breaks, you’ll wake up to the crisp mountain air
with snow-lined cliffs reflecting the morning light. Today’s walk is one of the
shortest on the trek, but also among the most rewarding. The trail follows the
lively river for a while, crossing over boulders and icy streams that add a
touch of adventure.</p>















<p class="MsoNormalM">A gentle but steady climb leads you to Pushtirang, a
beautiful alpine campsite surrounded by dramatic landscapes. From here,
panoramic views of towering peaks such as Nimish Khango, Tari Khango,
Hansbeshan, and even glimpses of the Pin Bhaba Pass will unfold before your
eyes.</p>















<p class="MsoNormalM">This high-altitude meadow, encircled by rugged mountains, is
the perfect spot to rest, acclimatize, and prepare for the challenging pass
crossing ahead. <br />
<br />
</p>                           </div>
