<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Day 5: Trek from Pushtirang to Pin Bhaba Pass &amp; down
to Mangrungse</b></p>















<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Stay:</b>
     Campsite at Mangrungse</li>
 <li><b>Trek
     Distance:</b> ~12 km</li>
 <li><b>Trek
     Duration:</b> 10–12 hours approx.</li>
 <li><b>Altitude:</b>
     Pushtirang – 4,100 m / 13,500 ft, Pin Bhaba Pass – 4,900 m / 16,100 ft,
     Mangrungse – 4,150 m / 13,600 ft</li>
 <li><b>Grade:</b>
     Moderate to Difficult</li>
</ul>















<p class="MsoNormalM">This is the highlight of your trek. From Pushtirang, a steep
climb leads you to Pin Bhaba Pass, the natural divide between Pin and Bhaba
valleys. Reaching the pass, you’ll witness a dramatic transformation from lush
meadows to the stark frozen desert of Spiti.</p>















<p class="MsoNormalM">The descent to Mangrungse is along a gravel trail, with a
foot crossing of the Pin River before reaching the serene campsite. The day is
challenging, but the views and sense of accomplishment make it unforgettable.</p>
















<p><br />
</p>                           </div>
