<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Day 6: Trek from Mangrungse to Mudh</b></p>















<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Stay:</b>
     Campsite / optional homestay at Mudh</li>
 <li><b>Trek
     Distance:</b> ~17 km</li>
 <li><b>Trek
     Duration:</b> 6–7 hours approx.</li>
 <li><b>Altitude:</b>
     Mangrungse – 4,150 m / 13,600 ft, Mudh – 3,750 m / 12,300 ft</li>
 <li><b>Grade:</b>
     Easy to Moderate (gradual descent)</li>
</ul>















<p class="MsoNormalM">The final day of the trek is relatively easier, with a
gradual descent from Mangrungse to Mudh. The trail passes through the Bara
Boulder campsite, where you’ll cross a Pin River tributary via a wooden bridge.
Continuing on, you’ll reach Pharka village and cross another small river before
arriving at Mudh.</p>















<span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Upon reaching Mudh, your trek concludes. Your
team leader will bid farewell here. You can choose to stay at a local homestay
or continue exploring nearby areas as per your plans.<br />
<br />
</span>                           </div>
